00:01:55.975 --> 00:01:57.955
And the step potential
is a potential

00:01:57.955 --> 00:02:02.350
that is 0 up to x equals 0.

00:02:02.350 --> 00:02:07.660
Here's the x-axis, and then
suddenly there's a step at v0.

00:02:11.490 --> 00:02:13.120
And here is the potential.

00:02:17.950 --> 00:02:23.330
But then the wave,
this is here, goes up.

00:02:23.330 --> 00:02:23.870
It's a step.

00:02:27.710 --> 00:02:33.450
And any energy eigenstates
here has to be bigger.

00:02:33.450 --> 00:02:37.320
The energy has to be
bigger than the lowest

00:02:37.320 --> 00:02:38.700
point of the potential.

00:02:38.700 --> 00:02:41.730
You know that, you kind
of have an energy that

00:02:41.730 --> 00:02:43.620
is like that less
because this would

00:02:43.620 --> 00:02:48.015
